<br>
Hord put forth the idea of AB being a side style instead of being at the end of the rear style chain.  <br>
<br>
Personally, I like the idea. However, my zerker just hit 50 a couple weeks ago and I never got to seriously try AB as a counter-parry style (not that anyone did, because of the parry bug).  I would still be interested to see how effective AB is in its origanal design.<br>
<br>
Here is  another thought I had:<br>
<br>
I personally never use Ravager-&gt;Atrophy-&gt;Decaying Rage/Scathing Blade.<br>
Here is my thinking, correct me please if I am wrong:<br>
First of all, Damage is too little at begining of the style.  Second, 3 chain styles take too long in RvR.  In PvE, the odds are you will parry or evade at some point in the chain and you will want to break it to do a stun or high damage polar light.  Last, if you have endurance regen you are just as well off spamming doublefrost.<br>
<br>
So, assuming that is at least semi-correct, the Ravager chain is really only usefull during early low-level PvE.<br>
<br>
So how about this:  Eliminate Decaying Rage and Scathing Blade for a new side based 2 style chain.<br>
<br>
Any other ideas?  Please let me know if you find DR/SB to be useful (I'll start using it! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hordgalahad>Hord Galahad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 11:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Styles</span><hr size=1> Just thought it would be an odd ball idea to throw out there.<br>
<br>
The AB style in it's previous form was a Nice ability to use when you were 1 on 1 (or dueling) In main RvR it was somewhat hard to get it off with everything happening and plus the fact that parry didn't work that much.<br>
<br>
Hard to say what would be the better of the 2 to have right now.<br>
<br>
With the parry form you have to be right on it in RvR make sure you hit your style and hope you beat their next style. Great for 1 on 1, not so great for groups of people fighting.<br>
<br>
With side you have to move to there side and get it off which is not to hard to get off when a bit of people are fighting. but hard if it is 1 on 1. <br>
<br>
Then again if you can get off a side style why not go for a back style... unless the side style does some nice damage... you know it being level 50 and all. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ulfhednar1>Ulfhednar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#000000>(6/12/03 1:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=112.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Styles</span><hr size=1> &quot;Personally, I like the idea. However, my zerker just hit 50 a couple weeks ago and I never got to seriously try AB as a counter-parry style (not that anyone did, because of the parry bug). I would still be interested to see how effective AB is in its origanal design.&quot;<br>
