<br>
The style damage between the two is close, with LA on average a bit higher.  Sword did more non-style damage.  However, with LA you attack much faster and use far less endurance.  Thus, you style more and you do way more damage.<br>
<br>
I have a fairly quick norse zerker, so possibly a slow troll zerk might want to frontload damage using a 2-handed weapon.  But I would think in most cases, the style question between LA and other lines is pretty much answered:  LA is the only thing that comes close even post patch.<br>
<br>
So this is what I think should be done given the ideas on this board:  <br>
<br>
Switch AB back to counter-parry, eliminate Scathing Blade and Decaying Rage and give us a 2-chain side style.<br>
<br>
It should be a semi-hard hitting chain with only minor effects (no stuns, DD's or serious bleeds) if any.  It should be weaker then our rear chain, since our rear chain is harder to execute, yet still deliver a large amount of damage to comply with our role as a light tank.<br>
