I have over 70 days on this Zerker and AB has always been my &quot;hard to hit&quot; style for pesky enemies like friars and other light tanks. It was also VERY useful in epic encounters with high level mobs that parry a ton.<br>
Now I've got a 3rd chain style that a barely ever use for RvR, and it can't be used on epic mobs in TG that actually get a heal off the damn cold proc!<br>
My PvE QB is:<br>
1)Snowblind -2)Polar Light -3)Frost Shadow -4)Snowsquall(filler) -5)Comeback -6)Doublefrost -7)Frosty Gaze -<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Bezerk IV -9) Purge -0) Ignore Pain<br>
<br>
Before patch it was:<br>
1)Snowblind -2)Comeback -3)Frosty Gaze -4)Polar Light -5)Frost Shadow -6)Doublefrost -7)Aurora Borealis -<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Bezerk IV -9) Purge -0) Ignore Pain<br>
<br>
I ditched the AB, and I moved the Comeback-FG chain to that position for consistency with the RvR QB. <br>
It looks like this:<br>
1)Conquer -2)Snowsquall -3)Icy Brilliance -4)Aurora Borealis -5)Comeback -6)Doublefrost -7)Frosty Gaze -<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Bezerk IV -9) Purge -0) Ignore Pain<br>
<br>
Prior to 1.62 I had the Snowsquall-IB chain nicely sitting in 4&amp;5 where the Polar Light-FS chain was, it kept locations consistent so I could just memorize the hotkeys. This was old RvR QB:<br>
<br>
1)Conquer -2)Comeback -3)Frosty Gaze -4)Snowsquall -5)Icy Brilliance -6)Doublefrost -7)Aurora Borealis -<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Bezerk IV -9) Purge -0) Ignore Pain<br>
<br>
I use Charge inplace of Conquer on an otherwise identical 3rd QB for 'no end' RvR.<br>
<br>
My typical 'all the time' attack was FG then Comeback backed with DF, it wont let you try a FG if you didnt land the Comeback and you have DF as backup. So usually I just DFed till I could land the FG chain then I'd move behind the target and do SS-IB. If I noticed the target parrying I could switch to AB-DF as my main attack and just try to get Comeback in when I saw/heard an evade. The Conquer is great for a fleeing target as it hinders them and lets you get SS-IB off a little easier.I guess this approach sounds complex, but it usually does a lot more damage than just mindlessly spamming DF, and if you don't have end regen spamming DF just isnt an option.<br>
<br>
So please, unless there are just throngs of rear chain maniacs out there landing all 3 styles let's try to get them to put AB back the way it was. Especially now that a target parrying is a lot more likely!<br>
<br>
